records.addlTxt:
Defendant Willie Lee Szulczewski in court with attorney Olya Petukhova.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Court sentenced defendant to serve 3 days in the House of Correction with credit for 3 days served FOR A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court ordered the defendant to submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge.  Court ordered defendant to pay ALL COSTS and SURCHARGES by 10-13-2015 or, as a penalty if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.

Defendant Willie Lee Szulczewski in court with attorney Olya Petukhova.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  The State's file is not in court.  Parties continue to work towards a resolution.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea in Branch 24.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 11, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Plea/sentencing hearing on September 4, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant Willie Lee Szulczewski in court with attorney Olya Petukhova.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 4, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Willie Lee Szulczewski in court with attorney Olya Petukhova.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 17, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
